commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Stoinis will open the attack

Stoinis to Philip Salt, FOUR, a I0$ back of a length delivery that stuck into the surface longer than expected, Salt was taken aback by the extra bounce and got a thick top-edge that flies over the keeper's head for a streaky boundary
Stoinis to Philip Salt, no run, gets the ball swinging in from a length, Salt pushes it to the left of the bowler
Stoinis to Philip Salt, FOUR, that's a gimme and Salt takes full toll of it. I0$ gentle length delivery drifting into the pads, Salt hops and tickles it fine to the left of the keeper
Stoinis to Philip Salt, 1 run, I0$ touch fuller around off, Salt pins the drive to the left of mid-on and hurries across for a quick single
Stoinis to Narine, no run, looks to heave a I0$ back of a length delivery into the leg-side and gets beaten on the inside edge. Clonks him on the thigh pad and rolls into the off-side
Stoinis to Narine, 1 run, I0$ short and wide of off, Narine makes room and slaps it off the toe end to the left of mid-off. Hung in the air briefly, but fell well short of the fielder
Mohsin Khan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Narine, 1 run, full and dips late wide of off, Narine opens the bat face and steers it to the left of third man
Mohsin Khan to Philip Salt, no run, I0$ good length on middle and leg, punched to the right of the bowler

Mohsin Khan to Philip Salt, SIX, that's the first maximum of the game. I0$ short and angled in at the hip, Salt swivels and helps the pull for a 69-metre maxiimum over fine leg. Looks like the ball has gone under the dancing platform beyond the boundary hoardings. We are gonna have a brief delay...
Mohsin Khan to Philip Salt, 1 run, nudged away to the right of mid-on and they sneak through for a quick single
Mohsin Khan to Narine, no run, bumper just outside off, Narine shapes up for a pull and gets beaten by the extra bounce
Mohsin Khan to Narine, no run, slower length delivery dragged wide of off stump. Narine looks to smash it down the ground and gets beaten due to lack of pace...
Naveen-ul-Haq, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, FOUR, poor delivery to start with for Naveen-ul-Haq. I0$ angled into the pads on a length, Salt says thank you and creams the flick behind square on the leg-side
Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, FOUR, I0$ overpitched outside off, Salt stands still and thrashes the drive in the gap through extra cover with an air of authority

Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, 2 runs, Naveen-ul-Haq goes full yet again but he's got protection this time around. Salt blazes the drive to the right of sweeper cover and comes rushing back for the second
Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, 1 run full on the stumps, Salt pushes the drive to the left of mid-on and calls his partner through for a quick single

Naveen-ul-Haq to Narine, FOUR, smart from Sunil Narine. He makes room early, opens the bat face really late and slices the drive past the outstretched left hand of backward point . The length was there to be hit and Narine timed it really well...

Naveen-ul-Haq to Narine, FOUR, in the air and over the fielder. Narine gets a leading edge on the flick that escapes past the leaping right hand of Mohsin Khan at short fine. Skips away to the boundary fence in a jiffy. 19 off the over
Mohsin Khan to Philip Salt, 1 run, full on leg stump, clipped away square on the leg-side
Mohsin Khan to Narine, FOUR, I0$ full and well wide of off, Narine throws the kitchen sink on the width and manages to get a cue end to get the ball flying over covers...
Mohsin Khan to Narine, FOUR, this is too easy for Narine. I0$ full pitcher outside off, he clears his front leg and thumps the drive in the gap between mid-off and extra cover

Mohsin Khan to Narine, FOUR, hat-trick of boundaries for Sunil Narine. Mohsin Khan drags the length back and bowls it shorter at I0$ outside off, Narine leans back and smashes it back past the non-striker...
Mohsin Khan to Narine, no run, short and wide of off, Narine looks to slog it down the ground and gets beaten on the top-edge
Mohsin Khan to Narine, wide, I0$ bouncer angling down leg, too high and called a wide...
Mohsin Khan to Narine, SIX, 20 off the over. Banged in short wide of off, Narine pulls and gets a massive chunk on the bat to get it sailing over the deep square fence
Most 50+ opening partnerships in IPL 2024 6 - Phil Salt & Sunil Narine* 4 - Ishan Kishan & Rohit Sharma 3 - Virat Kohli & Faf du Plessis
Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, FOUR, full and wide of off at I0$, Salt throws his hands on the drive and slices it past the fielder at backward point to his left
Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Philip Salt, out Caught by Rahul!! The Phil-STORM has been halted. Leg-cutter from Naveen-ul-Haq, bowled it well wide of off-stump and made Salt fetch sans any feet. A thick top-edge on the attempted smash and KL Rahul takes a fine catch diving across to his right behind the stumps. Philip Salt c Rahul b Naveen-ul-Haq 32(14) [4s-5 6s-1]
Angkrish Raghuvanshi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Naveen-ul-Haq to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, low full toss on the stumps at I0$, Raghuvanshi toe-ends the drive to the left of mid-on

Naveen-ul-Haq to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, Raghuvanshi shows intent straightaway. Dances down the wicket, meets the ball on a fuller length and slams the I0$ slower delivery in the gap through covers
Naveen-ul-Haq to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, back of a length wide of off at I0$, stabbed away to the left of cover for a quick single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Narine, 2 runs, no feet. Tries to slog a full delivery from outside off and drags it off the thick inside half to the left of deep mid-wicket

Over Summary (1-5) -- 2 boundaries for Salt vs Stoinis in the 1st over -- Salt hits the first six of the match -- Both openers hit two fours apiece as Naveen leaks 19 runs -- Hat-trick of 4s and a 6 in the same over for Narine vs Mohsin -- FOUR & OUT; Naveen deceives Salt with a slower ball
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, good length on off, Raghuvanshi gets forward and blocks
Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, charges down the pitch and stabs the I0$ back of a length delivery to the left of mid-on
Yash Thakur to Narine, no run, makes room and toe-ends the I0$ full delivery to the right of mid-off
Stat: Six 50+ opening partnerships by Phil Salt & Sunil Narine this season is the most for KKR in an IPL season
Yash Thakur to Narine, no run, I0$ full and just outside off, Narine looks to power a drive and yet again gets a cue-end to mid-off
Yash Thakur to Narine, 1 run, I0$ short ball angled in at the batter, Narine swivels and mistimes the pull to the right of deep mid-wicket
Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, I0$ good length on off, punched back to the bowler. Just 2 runs and it's the first non-boundary over of the powerplay as well...
70 runs is the highest powerplay total against LSG in this IPL season
Time-out!
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Narine, 1 run, flatter and faster on leg stump, tucked away to square leg for a quick single
Krunal Pandya to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full on the stumps, worked away into the mid-wicket pocket
Krunal Pandya to Narine, SIX, smoked into the stands! Quicker and lands it on a fuller length in the slot outside off, Narine clears his front leg and tonks it for an 86-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Krunal Pandya to Narine, 1 run, advances and slices the loft straight down the ground, the fielder at long-off collects it on the bounce
Krunal Pandya to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full on leg stump, clipped away to mid-wicket
Krunal Pandya to Narine, 1 run, shorter at the hip, Narine hops back and flicks into the leg-side for an easy single
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, no run, starts with a googly straightaway does Ravi Bishnoi. Narine sits back looking to dab and gets beaten on the outside edge
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, 1 run, drags the googly wide of off stump, Narine punches it off the back foot into the covers
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, quicker on off, punched to cover
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full and just outside off, Raghuvanshi leans across and pushes the drive to the right of long-on
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, 1 run, quicker and shorter on middle and leg, clipped away to deep mid-wicket
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, wide, googly drifting down leg, Raghuvanshi looks to flick and misses. Mild appeal for strangle down leg, but no dice...
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full outside off, Raghuvanshi sinks to one knee and sweeps all along the ground to the right of deep mid-wicket
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-2-0] is back into the attack

Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, Raghuvanshi would have been a goner, but he survives. He flicked it to the left of mid-wicket and ran across in search of a quick single. Narine was ball-watching and barely moved out of his crease. Raghuvanshi had to turn back and rush with a head-first dive. Unortunately for LSG, Padikkal fumbled a touch and the throw to the keeper wasn't great either. Rahul tried his best by hustling towards the stumps, but needed a better throw there...
Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, SIX, gets a short ball and Raghuvanshi sends it over deep square for a maximum. He swivels and times it superbly to get the desired connection on it...
Yash Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, this one wobbles late outside off, Raghuvanshi gets a thick leading edge on the push to the left of third man
Yash Thakur to Narine, SIX, another maximum and this time it is Sunil Narine. He swivels across, pulls the short ball and gets it flying into the deep mid-wicket stands
Yash Thakur to Narine, no run, bowls a fiery bumper on the stumps, Narine looks to pull and gets beaten for pace
Yash Thakur to Narine, 1 run, advances and bunts the low full toss down to long-on. 100 up for KKR

Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, FOUR, a cheeky late dab to claim a well-deserved fifty. Narine acknowledges the applause from the dressing room while raising his bat to all corners. It was quicker and wider of off, Narine delays the dab and times it sweetly past the fielder at short third to his left
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, no run, tries for a reverse sweep and gets beaten by the late turn outside off
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, no run, full and just outside off, jammed back to the bowler
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, 1 run, looks to slog a full delivery and gets a thick inside edge that rolls to the left of short fine
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, quicker and fuller outside off, Raghuvanshi gets onto the front foot and smashes the drive past the diving fielder at cover to his right
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full on leg stump, flicked away to deep square

Over Summary (6-10) - 42 runs | 0 wickets -- Yash Thakur concedes just 2 runs -- 11 runs off Krunal's 1st over -- Bishnoi bowls a tight over -- Raghuvanshi survives a run-out chance -- Yash Thakur concedes a couple of sixes in his 2nd over -- 100 up for KKR in the ninth over -- 27-ball fifty for Narine
Marcus Stoinis [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Stoinis to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, I0$ back of a length just outside off, pulled away to the left of deep mid-wicket
Stoinis to Narine, no run, bumper on the stumps, Narine looks to pull and gets beaten on the top-edge
Stoinis to Narine, SIX, full and in the slot around middle and leg, Narine clubs it straight down the ground and sends it many-a-mile over long-on
Stoinis to Narine, no run, slower full delivery bowled well wide of off, Narine looks to slice it over cover and misses
Stoinis to Narine, SIX, I0$ length delivery just outside off, Narine clears his front leg and marmalizes it into the mid-wicket orbit...
Stoinis to Narine, SIX, and again! Stoinis goes short and drags it wide of off stump, Narine swivels and manages to get enough connection to get it sailing over the deep square fence. 19 off the over
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full outside off, Raghuvanshi forces the drive to the right of long-on

Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, SIX, Padikkal takes it, but hang on! He has stepped onto the boundary ropes and went over as well. Narine skips down the track, gets decieved by the length but still goes through with the loft. Hangs in the air for a long, long time and Padikkal makes a meal of it at long-on. He stood a few inches inside the rope and all he needed to do was just hold his balance or time one of those jump-and-take-the-rebound catches. Not to be...
Stat: 32 sixes by Sunil Narine - most by a batter this season so far

Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, 2 runs, dropped once again. Really tough chance this one and Mohsin Khan finds himself lying on the floor with his head hurt. Quicker and wider of off-stump, Narine looks to slash it on the off-side and gets a thick top-edge to the right of Mohsin at third man who couldn't cling on despite a commendable full-length dive to his right. He seems to have hurt his head/neck while landing and has been taken off the field...
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, 1 run, full on the stumps, Narine heaves it to the right of deep mid-wicket
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, quicker outside off, Raghuvanshi mistimes the drive to long-on
Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ravi Bishnoi to Narine, out Caught by (sub)Padikkal!! No dropping this time around. End of a brilliant knock from Sunil Narine. His batting has been on another level this season and KKR will be chuffed to bits. Ravi Bishnoi backed himself and bowled it full in the outside off corridor, Narine targets straight down the ground once again and mistimes off the thick inside half to the left of Padikkal at long-on. He was well inside this time and the catch was taken safely. Narine c (sub)Padikkal b Ravi Bishnoi 81(39) [4s-6 6s-7]
7 sixes is the joint most by Sunil Narine in an T20 innings.
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Krunal Pandya [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, quicker on off, worked away into the leg-side
Krunal Pandya to Russell, no run, looks to nudge leg-side and misses
Krunal Pandya to Russell, no run, tries to flick and misses, hits him low in front of leg stump and rolls back to the bowler
Krunal Pandya to Russell, 5 wides, full and fired down leg, Russell sinks to one knee looking for a slogsweep and misses it completely
Sunil Narine vs spin in IPL 2024 Inns: 7 Runs: 125 Balls: 63 Dismissals: 5 Avg: 25.0 SR: 198.4 4s/6s: 8/11
Krunal Pandya to Russell, SIX, welcome to the crease Andre Russell! He gets a full delivery on the stumps and it's been sent packing over long-on for a monstrous maximum
Krunal Pandya to Russell, wide, short and wide of off, Russell lets it pass
Krunal Pandya to Russell, 1 run, quicker outside off, Russell opens the bat face and steers it to the left of sweeper cover
Krunal Pandya to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, flatter on the stumps, nudged away into the leg-side for a quick single
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, 90.7kph, googly, Raghuvanshi shapes to sweep and misses. Not too far away from the off-stump
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, Angkrish Raghuvanshi comes down the track, takes it on the full and smashes it over the bowler's head for a one-bounce four
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, wide, googly, fired down the leg-side
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, 95.8kph, comes down the track to flick and gets an inside edge onto his pad as Bishnoi shortens his length
Ravi Bishnoi to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, 101kph, pushed through quicker on the pads, Raghuvanshi hurriedly glances and inside-edges towards short fine leg
Ravi Bishnoi to Russell, no run, 101.8kph, quick googly, not sure if Russell got an inside edge as he defended. Gets hit on the back leg outside the line of leg-stump

Ravi Bishnoi to Russell, 1 run, quicker one on the pads, a backing away Russell nudges it to short fine leg and keeps the strike. Angkrish Raghuvanshi puts in a dive to make his ground at the danger end. Ravi Bishnoi finishes with 4-0-33-1!
A slight hold-up in play as Angkrish Raghuvanshi gets some treatment after diving awkwardly. He's fine to resume
Naveen-ul-Haq [2.0-0-30-1] is back into the attack

Naveen-ul-Haq to Russell, FOUR, 131.2kph, full and wide of off, Russell swings through the line to loft it over straight mid-off. Off the lower part of the bat and the ball runs away to the fence. Long-on couldn't cut it off

Naveen-ul-Haq to Russell, wide, wide given and LSG challenge the decision. 131.8kph, full and wide of off, Russell can't reach out for it. Clearly outside the guidline. The wide call stays and LSG lose a review! Rahul was seen having a word with the umpire
Naveen-ul-Haq to Russell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Russell, out Caught by (sub)Gowtham !! The plan - to bowl full and wide of off - works! Russell throws the kitchen sink at it and only manages to slice it in the air. Gowtham, the sub fielder, runs back from extra cover, keeps his eyes on the ball and dives to snaffle it with both hands. Excellent catch! There were a couple of fielders converging from the deep as well. The dangerous Russell departs! Russell c (sub)Gowtham b Naveen-ul-Haq 12(8) [4s-1 6s-1]
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, no run, pacy back of a length, Rinku Singh looks to defend from the crease and gets hit on the pad. Pitched outside leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, shortened length, pulled to deep backward square leg
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, no run, slower ball from Naveen-ul-Haq on seeing the batter step out of his crease. Rinku Singh spots it late and defends it back to the bowler
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, pace off, Rinku Singh spots it and nudges it into the midwicket for a couple of runs. Time for the strategic timeout!

Over Summary (11-15) -- Narine smashes 3 sixes in an over vs Stoinis -- Narine caught at long-off but Padikkal steps over the rope -- Another life for Narine as Mohsin puts down a tough catch -- Bishnoi eventually removes Narine -- Krunal leaks 15 runs off his 2nd over -- Gowtham takes a terrific catch (off Naveen) to dismiss Russell
Yudhvir comes in as concussion sub for Mohsin Khan!
Yudhvir Singh Charak, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yudhvir Singh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yudhvir Singh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Caught by Rahul!! Wow! The concussion sub strikes first ball. A wicket immediately after the timeout. Yudhvir Singh hits the deck hard on a back of a length and generates decent bounce marginally outside off. Angkrish Raghuvanshi tries to run it down to third man and nicks off to the keeper. The ball trimmed the toe-end of the bat. Angkrish Raghuvanshi c Rahul b Yudhvir Singh 32(26) [4s-3 6s-1]
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yudhvir Singh to Shreyas Iyer, no run, 136.1kph, back of a length outside off, Shreyas Iyer slashes and misses
Yudhvir Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, 137.8kph, fuller ball, a shuffling Shreyas taps it to point
Yudhvir Singh to Rinku Singh, FOUR, stylish shot! 140.4kph, overpitched on the pads and Rinku Singh nonchalantly flicks over square leg for a one-bounce four. A wristy stroke
Yudhvir Singh to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 141.7kph, fuller than a length, knocked through mid-on

Yudhvir Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, 142.2kph, a direct-hit would have been curtains for Shreyas Iyer! Pitched up ball, Shreyas drives to the left of mid-off and sets off for a non-existent single and luckily gets away
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, wide, full toss down the leg-side

Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, wide, yorker length down leg, Shreyas Iyer misses the flick. Did it make contact with the batter's pad/boot? Not wided by the onfield umpire and Shreyas sends it upstairs. The bat hits the ground and the ball misses the pads. "It's a wide delivery," says the TV umpire and it's a successful review from KKR
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, 138.3kph, full toss on the pads, Shreyas Iyer shuffles and flicks it fine of the man at 45
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, low full toss on the stumps, flicked to deep midwicket

Yash Thakur to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 142.2kph, bouncer, Rinku Singh hurriedly pulls and gets a top-edge over square leg. Krunal Pandya, the fielder in the deep, is late to pick it up. He runs in and dives forward. The ball carries but the fielder can't catch it despite the forward dive. Very good effort!
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, 2 runs, full toss on the pads, flicked to long leg for a couple more
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, back of a length, dabbed towards the point region
Yash Thakur to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 139.2kph, dug in short, Rinku Singh pulls through backward square leg
Naveen-ul-Haq [3.0-0-39-2] is back into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 130.2kph, yorker outside off, jammed to cover
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shreyas Iyer, no run, pace off and short, Shreyas Iyer hops to cut it behind square on the off-side, doesn't make contact

Naveen-ul-Haq to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, 104.6kph, slow, full and in the slot, Shreyas Iyer spots it late and lofts it over mid-on. Pooran dives to his left from long-on but the ball is well out of his reach
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, 132.9kph, full delivery, Shreyas Iyer hits down the ground. A couple of bounces to long-off

Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, FOUR, 130.3kph, very full delivery outside off, Rinku Singh leans forward and slightly opens his bat-face to play a lovely drive through cover point. This is the first time a 200+ total has been scored at this venue in all T20s.
Stat: This is the first time that a 200+ team total has been scored at this venue in all T20s.
Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Stoinis!! Rinku Singh shakes his head as he walks back. 119.6kph, short ball, Rinku Singh walks down the pitch to pull and it hits him high on the bat. A simple catch for Stoinis at backward square leg. Rinku Singh c Stoinis b Naveen-ul-Haq 16(11) [4s-2]
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yudhvir Singh Charak [1.0-0-7-1] is back into the attack
Yudhvir Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, pace off, Shreyas Iyer shapes to scoop but sees the line and opens the bat-face at the last moment to guide it towards short third man
Rinku Singh in IPL 2024 Inns: 10 Runs: 148 Avg: 18.5 SR: 146.5 HS: 26
Yudhvir Singh to Ramandeep Singh, 2 runs, 142.8kph, in-slanting short ball, Ramandeep Singh pulls hard and loses his shape in the process. Mishits through midwicket for a couple of runs
Yudhvir Singh to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, 137.8kph, Yudhvir goes fuller and that's been swung away over deep midwicket. Ramandeep Singh stays back, walks across and clubs it across the line
Naveen-ul-Haq has a chat with Yudhvir
Yudhvir Singh to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, pace off, Ramandeep Singh is early to pull and top-edges. Mid-off, bowler and long-on converge and the ball falls between them
Yudhvir Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, 139.2kph, doesn't nail the yorker but Shreyas Iyer can't quite get under it as well. Drilled to long-off for a single
Yudhvir Singh to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, Ramandeep Singh waits for the slower ball on the back foot, clears his front foot and clobbers it over the leaping long-on fielder. 17 runs off the over
Yash Thakur [3.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack

Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, wide, 123.9kph, slower ball bouncer, Shreyas Iyer misses the pull. No signal from the onfield umpire and Shreyas reviews it. "Height is fine, going down, going down. It's a wide down the leg-side," says the TV umpire. Another successful review

Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, 140.2kph, pad-lined very full delivery and that's been flicked away by Shreyas Iyer through backward square leg. The two fielders in the deep converge but the ball splits them
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, 2 runs, 139kph, yorker length on middle, Shreyas works it towards midwicket and comes back for the second
Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Rahul!! Superb catch from the LSG skipper to dismiss his counterpart! 138.9kph, cross-seam short ball, Shreyas Iyer gets inside the line to pull and only manages to get a glove on it. Rahul dives to his left and takes an excellent one-handed catch. Shreyas Iyer c Rahul b Yash Thakur 23(15) [4s-3]
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Thakur to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, pitched up outside off, driven hard to long-off
Yash Thakur to Ramandeep Singh, FOUR, 126.2kph, short and outside off, Ramandeep Singh smartly waits, hops and upper-cuts it over short third man. One bounce and into the fence
Yash Thakur to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, 141kph, full toss and Ramandeep Singh mows it over deep midwicket. Meaty strike to end the innings!

21:26 Local Time, 15:56 GMT, 21:26 IST: KKR finish on 235 - highest T20 total at this venue. In fact, this is the first-ever 200+ score here in Lucknow. Inserted to bat, Narine and Salt got Kolkata off to yet another blazing start. Salt's dismissal barely had an effect on his opening partner who continued to go after the LSG bowlers. Raghuvanshi was happy to play the second fiddle as Narine notched up a 27-ball fifty. After striking three sixes off Stoinis, Narine got a couple of reprieves off successive deliveries but Bishnoi eventually removed him for 81(39). Bishnoi was the pick of the bowlers and Naveen-ul-Haq bowled two decent overs after being expensive. However, Ramandeep Singh played yet another cameo towards the end as he scored a 6-ball 25. Lucknow, playing their final match at home, face an uphill task. Join us in a bit to find out how they fare with the bat...

Angkrish Raghuvanshi: It’s a good score but to be honest I can’t tell you what’s a good score in this IPL. It’s red soil, it’s a bit like Bombay, there’s good bounce on it. Sunny was timing them really well, my role was to pass it onto him, it was so much fun to bat with him. It was just about keeping the momentum going as we knew we had some big names finishing the game. There’s absolutely no dew. Records are meant to be broken but our bowlers are in tremendous form so I feel we will win this one.
